reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 10, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great design, sturdy, but with an assembly caution
reviews.reviewText: First the good news. This table is remarkable in its design -- it is higher than many more expensive models, quite sturdy, and for its economic size has a lot of placing/storing potential for books, drinks, glasses, and whatever else you would want. And it moves, easily. I am pleased, as I viewed many other side tables that cost more and seemed to offer less.Now for the assembly caution. All the parts are labeled, but the pictures are small and the directions sparse. So it began: attach sides to the bottom (I believe B to A). OK, that was easy enough. But then nothing fit and I began to feel this table was cheap for a reason. And I was working alone, so the pieces would not always stay in place for ease of attachment. I felt frustrated, paused, took a deep breath, and then...of course, those four holes go on the bottom for the wheels. You can't see it in the picture. So I started over and the whole project went much more smoothly. Then I put on the two top wood pieces, and as a previous reviewer stated, they didn't match up. I didn't like that. So I stopped, breathed, and...why not switch out the two? I did so and they matched quite well. There is not instruction for this, it's a 50% chance of getting it right. But after my first error it just seemed possible there was more than one way these could fit. And, like I said earlier, I am quite satisfied with the result.
